üß† 7. ASSEMBLY PROCESS
Step 1: Component Placement

Fix the ESP32 + GPS module in a small plastic case on the shoe‚Äôs side.

Mount the Ultrasonic sensor at the toe/front area for forward obstacle detection.

Place the vibration motor near the heel or ankle for maximum tactile feedback.

Position temperature and pressure sensors under the insole (inside the shoe).

Step 2: Wiring and Connections

Connect all components using thin, flexible jumper wires.

Ensure insulation to avoid short circuits.

Route the wires neatly along the shoe‚Äôs edges.

Step 3: Circuit Integration

Assemble connections on a small Zero PCB or mini breadboard.

Power the setup with the Li-ion battery through a TP4056 charging circuit.

Add a small on/off toggle switch for power control.

Step 4: Testing & Calibration

Power ON the shoe.

Test GPS data transmission on Blynk map widget.

Place an obstacle in front of the ultrasonic sensor to verify buzzer/vibration response.

Check temperature and pressure values on the dashboard.

Step 5: Final Enclosure & Finishing

Place all modules inside the enclosure.

Add foam or padding to protect components and maintain comfort.

Use fabric glue or stitching to secure the system to the shoe base.

Workflow:

Initialize sensors and GPS.

Connect ESP32 to Wi-Fi network.

Continuously read sensor and GPS data.

Send real-time data to Blynk dashboard.

Trigger alerts when threshold values are crossed.

